programme.desc: Stories of witchcraft, murder and human sacrifice bring the team to Treasure Holt. Derek is guided by the spirit of a monk and contacts two of the ghosts seen in what was once a house of disrepute.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Derby Gaol
programme.desc: Historian Richard Felix joins Yvette and the team as they are locked inside Derby Gaol, where scenes of total incarceration and brutal executions have taken place since 1756.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Aldwych Underground Station
programme.desc: Yvette and Jason dress up in 1940s army uniforms as they investigate Aldwych Station, which was built after demolishing a theatre in 1907, and used as an air raid shelter during WWII.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Charleville Forest Castle
programme.desc: Located in the center of Ireland, Charleville Forest Castle is built on the site of an ancient burial ground where plague victims were buried in the 1700s. The team holds a Victorian-style séance.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Michelam Priory
programme.desc: Michelam Priory was originally a church built on a medieval moated island. In 1556 it was transformed into a house where many families have lived through history and tragedy.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Children's Children
programme.desc: A reporter uncovers a secret about the past of a woman who runs a home for unwed mothers.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Friends
programme.desc: While working as a substitute teacher at a high school, Jonathan assigns an overweight girl to tutor a troubled baseball star.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Special Love - Part 1
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark persuade a youngster with Down's Syndrome to join the Special Olympics.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Special Love - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark's friend Scotty wants to adopt the boy with Down's Syndrome. A custody battle occurs with the biological parents.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: For the Love of Larry
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark rescue victims trapped in a car, thanks to a helpful dog.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Another Kind of War, Another Kind of Peace
programme.desc: A man whose son died in Vietnam learns that he has an Amerasian grandson.
programme.sub-title: Another Kind of War, Another Kind of Peace

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: That's Our Dad
programme.desc: A children's-show host has a warm-hearted TV persona but is actually a cynic at heart.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Trials of Tracy
programme.desc: Tracy is a New York City lawyer who can't find a man. Her frumpy wardrobe and thick glasses keep her home buried in her books for fear of rejection. But our team is on the case to bring this lonely lawyer out of her shell and gain some needed confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jayne Lowe
programme.desc: Woking wife and mother Jayne Lowe is at an all time low. After a high-flying career as an air-hostess, she has come down to earth with a bump, as a stay-at-home mum of three under-five's. Can Nicki Hambleton-Jones make Jayne look ten years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Reconstructing Bernie
programme.desc: A construction worker by trade, Bernie is a man's man. So while years of backbreaking labor in the sun has taken its toll on his body, Bernie hasn't been taking care of himself. Time to make Bernie look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Donna Fuller
programme.desc: Derby wife and mum Donna Fuller is stuck at home and stuck in a rut. Her biggest problem is her gapped front teeth, which have left her, literally, with nothing to smile about. Can Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team make Debbie look 10 years younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Bikini Special - Heather Williams
programme.desc: NHS Manager Heather Williams is the perfect candidate: after a weight loss of five stones and three years of four times a week gym workouts, all that remained of her former size 20 body was a sack of excess skin covering a tiny 4 foot eleven frame.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Singing A New Tune
programme.desc: April lost a front tooth in a horseback riding accident and never smiles. Her passion is singing, and she'd like to stand on stage without embarrassment. Will an orthodontic overhaul and a full Glam assault drop years from her appearance?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Independence Day
programme.desc: Recently divorced and about to send her daughter off to college, Candice is embarking on a new phase in life. Alone and worried about feeling old and unattractive, Candice has come for help to boost her spirits.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Debbie Ashcroft "One Year On"
programme.desc: 46 year old Debbie Ashcroft was a lifelong smoker and sunbed addict with the peculiar habit of bleaching her hair up to six times a week. A year later Nicky visits Debbie to find out if she's permanently kicked all the bad habits.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Sewing The Seeds To A New Look
programme.desc: Melissa has the perfect Beverly Hills fashion career, working with the finest made-to-order clothing. But when the exclusive clientele see her missing teeth, the impression is not what she would like. She also desperately wants to update her look.
programme.sub-title: Sewing The Seeds To A New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: 80 lbs. Down, 10 Years To Go
programme.desc: After struggling with health issues Cheryl has recently lost 80 pounds and needs her appearance to catch up to her body. She is single and ready to start dating again. Cheryl's new makeover will help her hit the dating scene with a renewed attitude.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Grey Skies To Blue
programme.desc: Between her busy family life, and a scrapbook business on the side, Christine barely has time for herself. After 20 years of marriage and three kids, she's in need of a makeover and some serious rekindled romance.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Prescription For Youth
programme.desc: New Mom Amber has her work cut out for her. In her early teens she was diagnosed with Crohn's disease, which resulted in unwanted physical side effects. Watch the team of experts make Amber look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Time to Face the Music
programme.desc: Akil is an unemployed music industry executive who feels like his under eye bags, to long dread locks and older looks are getting in the way of getting a new job. 10 Years Younger is on one of it's hardest missions to date!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Looking for Love Through All the Wrong Glasses
programme.desc: Will owns a successful real estate investment business, but he hasn't been as lucky in love. Will's phobia of doctors have kept him from losing his thick glasses and fixing his gnarled teeth. The bottom line is that Will hasn't had a date in years!
programme.sub-title: Looking for Love Through All the Wrong Glasses

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Business is looking up at Leopard's Den but Sarah is feeling agitated. Caroline thinks it because Simon, her ex husband and Evan and Olivia's Dad, is arriving from England to get married. But Sarah has other things on her mind.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Danny is undertaking a drugs trial at Leopard's Den. But de-worming wildebeest isn't Caroline's idea of fun. She hates animals and finds the whole business mind-numbingly boring.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Du Plessis is in a foul mood. It's his 60th birthday and he has no intentions of celebrating it. But the Trevanions have other ideas and Caroline is organising a surprise party.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: All is quiet at Leopard's Den as Sarah, Evan and Olivia gather at the hospital. Danny has been given the all clear to go home. But Du Plessis is still unconscious and seriously ill. Caroline keeps a tender vigil at his bedside.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: New lodges nearly break the family, but they learn that it's the animals which make Leopard's Den a success.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny needs an assistant but fails to see that she's right under his nose; Sarah finds out that she needs her mum.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den expands and DuPlessis becomes a grandfather after a close-call with an angry elephant.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 3
programme.desc: Music journalist, Illario the Lothario, is one of many foreign revelers who have come unstuck. His passport is drenched and no longer valid. He arrives to the Embassy, only to fall head over heals for a dashing Thai diplomat.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4
programme.desc: Best mates Rhys and Benny, are on their first-ever overseas holiday together. They're staying in the heart of Phuket and the sky's the limit. They've done everything their parents warned them not to.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5
programme.desc: When a massive earthquake strikes Nepal hundreds of traumatised and injured Aussie travellers need to be evacuated to Thailand. 19-year-old Alex from Sydney is in Phuket for a kickboxing holiday with his mates.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6
programme.desc: When disaster strikes, and a ferry sinks off the coast of Krabi carrying 104 passengers the Embassy goes into overdrive. Callum heads to the immigration detention centre to check on the welfare of a serial visa-overstay offender.

programme.title: The Embassy
programme.desc: Queenslander Sam and his German girlfriend Sandra met and fell in love in Thailand. After a long distance relationship, they've finally decided to leave their respective countries and begin a life together in Chiang Mail.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 8
programme.desc: Former school teacher Jacob has been locked up in a Thai prison for the past 9 months, awaiting trial for a high grade drug trafficking offence. Young Maroubra-boy James arrives at the Embassy for a new passport claiming it was lost.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: It is the most extraordinary case diplomat Tom Walter has ever seen - 18 and 16 year-old Aussie brothers, Aiden and Jackson have been abandoned by their parents and left to fend for themselves.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 2
programme.desc: It's judgement day for abandoned Aussie brothers, Aiden and Jackson. After hours of questioning, Indonesian Immigration officials have confiscated the boy's passports and put them under strict house arrest.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 3
programme.desc: Jenny's holiday has turned into a nightmare - she was collecting her son's dirty laundry from his hotel room in Bali and got caught up in a surprise Immigration raid. Authorities have confiscated her passport and now Jenny is stuck.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4
programme.desc: 59-year-old Joanne came to Thailand for a body makeover. She's had a tummy tuck and liposuction to look her best for her daughter's wedding. She loses her passport and the wound from her tummy tuck gets infected, Joanne finds herself stuck in Thailand.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5
programme.desc: Wayne has no money, no passport and a mountain of debt. Homeless and out of options, he's back at the Consulate in Bali with sobering news. But can consular officer, Tom Walter trust his story?

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 12
programme.desc: Great cars and pretty girls. The Nürburgring is shaking as the VLN begins its second leg of the tournament. We will be commentating on this exciting competition, as well as showing highlights of the BMW's 1st leg win.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 13
programme.desc: The fourth race of the VLN season is regarded as a dress rehearsal for the 24 hour race. For the top teams and best drivers this is the last opportunity for a real hard test.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 14
programme.desc: Today, we are going to look back at the highlight of last week. The 24 hour race - as always it was exciting. In addition 'Strong Man Run' and a look at the tourist drivers.

programme.title: Track Masters
programme.desc: Some heavy guns are going to be driven around the ring on today's show. We are at the Truck Grand Prix and shall be following the progress of driver Uwe Nittle as he gets ready for qualifying.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 16

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 17
programme.desc: Now that the 24-hour race is over we have left the Nürburgring and moved to Büren, Germany, where Räder Sport is based. Famous for really fast front-wheel drives, it provides a lot of horsepower down on the track.

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 18

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 19

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 21

programme.title: Track Masters: Episode 22

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: First of its Kind

programme.desc: Siobhan falls while rock climbing. As the others search for her, she dreams that she is on trial for supporting the Taelons. Zo'or questions whether Sandoval's CVI imperative to serve the Taelons has broken down as others are experiencing.

programme.desc: The drought finally throws up a fire and the wedding turns into a firefight for everyone. The omens are bad.

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: Tragedy strikes and the Trevanians have to decide what future lies ahead of them in these difficult times.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: It's a year since we left Leopard's Den and much has changed. The animal hospital has been rebuilt and is now up and running. It's a big day for all the family as Danny has been fighting for custody of Evan and today they will learn the judge's decision.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny and Evan's life on the run doesn't start well when Danny falls asleep at the wheel and drives into a ditch. They have to enlist a local farmer, Johann, to winch them out.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5
programme.desc: Wayne has no money, no passport and a mountain of debt. Homeless and out of options, he's back at the Consulate in Bali with sobering news. But can consular officer, Tom Walter trust his story?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6
programme.desc: 56-year-old Michael is living every parent's worst nightmare. His six-year-old son Dylan has been missing for three months now. His ex-wife didn't return him after a routine weekend visit and now he fears that she's trying to smuggle him out of Bali.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 7
programme.desc: Family man Laurie, an offshore oil rigger, is fresh out of jail and claims he's been framed. He's been charged with causing grievous bodily harm after he was involved in a backstreet brawl 12 months ago. Consular officer, Val is on the case.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 8
programme.desc: Aussie expat, Roger arrives at the Embassy after being robbed by a Lady Boy. He says the Lady Boy burst into his hotel room and stole $800 Aussie dollars, along with his drivers licence and international money cards.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 9
programme.desc: Retired construction worker, Ivan, has come to the Embassy with a major financial problem. He purchased a luxury condo in Phuket two years ago, but he still hasn't received the ownership papers from the developer. And it's not looking good.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 10
programme.desc: Mark came to Bali 18 months ago to setup an I.T. business with his Indonesian wife. But unbeknownst to Mark, his passport contains a fake immigration stamp that was issued by a fake immigration agent.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save two teenage girls fighting for their lives after their car crashed and rolled the Waiwera Hill.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: Professional scuba diver Brian Green has been found floating and not breathing, and is on a boat near the Noises, a group of islands in the Hauraki Gulf. The team has to move fast.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: On Great Mercury Island near Coromandel, a scuba diver has surfaced unconscious without a pulse. Without Rescue 1 he may soon be dead.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team respond to a call out where an elderly couple in their 60s are in a critical condition after a head on collision.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: A truck driver who had one leg amputated 40 years ago, has crashed his truck and crushed his remaining leg. If Rescue 1 can't get him to hospital in time, he will bleed to death.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: Westpac chopper paramedic Bruce Kerr has a frantic battle to save a car crash victim with a life-threatening head injury.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save a 39 year old forestry worker who has been struck on the head leaving him paralyzed from the waist down.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: The chopper crew races to save a woman with a rare disease who's in danger of suffocating from uncontrollable muscle spasms; a badly burnt toddler at Cooks Beach needs an urgent airlift to hospital.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: The chopper team is called out to save a pilot who's trapped in the wreck of his hang glider and a diabetic bus driver is found seriously ill after four days lying on his floor.

programme.title: Tuning: Dodge / Mini Cooper / Porsche
programme.desc: The Dodge RAM is anything but cute. It is a true beast. The ram is the symbol of the Dodge brand and the eponym for a very special vehicle. The RAM pickup combines robustness and impulsiveness.

programme.title: Tuning: Lamborghini / Porsche / Jaguar
programme.desc: A supercharger from O.CT gives the Lamborghini Huracan, which is by no means underpowered, an additional 200 hp. This makes the super sports car the ultimate street-legal projectile.

programme.title: 4x4: Wildly through the desert
programme.desc: In 2010, BMW and the German racing team X-Raid decided to transform a Mini Countryman into an offroad-vehicle and participate in the world-famous Dakar Rally. Also: the Mercedes G63 AMG 6x6, a most exclusive, over-the-top 6-wheel off-road monster...

programme.title: 4x4: Trendy City - SUVs
programme.desc: City-SUVs are the latest trend in the automotive world. They aren't necessarily made for offroad terrain but attract customers through their modern and urban design. In this episode, the Subaru XV shows its offroad skills, and the Nissan Juke is take…

programme.title: 4x4: Land Rover Special
programme.desc: The Land Rover Defender is one of the oldest offroad car models. It may be loud and uncomfortable, but it's absolutely authentic in its simplicity. We took a look at this iconic vehicle and 70 years of Land Rover history.

programme.title: 4x4: Extraordinary SUVs
programme.desc: This Mitsubishi Outlander Plug-In Hybrid is the world's first hybrid SUV with two electric motors and a 2-liter combustion engine. We tested if such a combination makes sense for offroad vehicles. Also: the Chevrolet Silverado...

programme.title: 4x4: SUV Girlpower
programme.desc: Nancy and Nadia, two daring Jordanian women faced the challenge to cross the Moroccan desert in a Hummer H3. The two professional racers took part in the Conti 4x4 Trophy - a demanding rally through the Atlas Mountains and the Western Sahara.

programme.title: 4x4: SUV Concepts
programme.desc: Before Bentley and Jaguar started producing their own luxury SUV models, the two British brands presented their take on this special range of cars. We took a look at their concept cars, the Bentley EXP 9F and Jaguar's C-X17.

programme.title: 4x4: Normal vs. Lifestyle SUVs
programme.desc: The SUVs Nissan X-Trail and BMW X4 certainly aren't typical offroaders. We witnessed Nissan's presentation of their new X-Trail model and the BMW X4 world premiere in Bilbao. Also: the Steinbeißer Trophy...

programme.title: 4x4: American SUVs
programme.desc: In the United States, SUVs aren't usually considered simple workhorses but rather treated as regular everyday vehicles. US-Americans don't want to miss out on space, comfort and loading capacity. Their motto is: the bigger, the better.

programme.title: 4x4: Tuned SUVs
programme.desc: SUVs usually are rather impressive right out of the factory, but there are many tuning and customizing options: huge wheels, crazy colors and perfomance similar to super sports cars. One might ask if such alterations are really necessary, but enthusi…

programme.title: 4x4: Small, strong, stylish
programme.desc: At first glance, compact cars like the Audi A1, the Volkswagen Golf and the Mini don't seem to belong in this series, but when the "A1" becomes the "S1" and the Golf gets a "R" in its name, these small cars turn into all-wheel beasts.

programme.title: 4x4: Fascination offroad
programme.desc: At the All-Wheel Adventure in Bad Kissingen, Germany, the biggest exhibition for offroaders in Europe, we test drove the Rallye Defender and examined how a regular Jeep Wrangler with only a few modifications could double in price.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Friendly Fire
